# Request

```json
{
  "clientKey": "YOUR_API_KEY", // Get API_KEY from https://NoCaptchaAi.com
  "task": {
    "type": "ImageToTextTask",
    "module": "common", // "module_001", "module_002", ...
    "images": [""], // string(single) or array(multiple) of base64 of the main images // string(single) or array(multiple) of base64 of the main images // string(single) or array(multiple) of base64 of the main images
    "websiteURL": "website URL", // source url to improve accuracy
    "phrase": false,
    "case": true,
    "numeric": 0,
    "math": false,
    "minLength": 1,
    "maxLength": 5,
    "score": 0.8, // 0.8 ~ 1 expected matching score
    "comment": "enter the text you see on the image"
  },
  "languagePool": "en"
}
```

# Response

```json
{ 
"errorId": 0,
"solution": { "text": [ "VCMS" ] },
"status": "ready",
"taskId": ""
}

```

<TabItem label="JavaScript">

```js
const axios = require("axios");

const url = "https://api.nocaptchaai.com/createTask";

const payload = {
  clientKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
  task: {
    type: "ImageToTextTask",
    module: "common",
    body: "[base64image]",
    websiteURL: "website URL",
    phrase: false,
    case: true,
    numeric: 0,
    math: false,
    minLength: 1,
    maxLength: 5,
    score: 0.8,
    comment: "enter the text you see on the image",
  },
  languagePool: "en",
};

axios
  .post(url, payload, {
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
  })
  .then((response) => {
    console.log(response.data);
  })
  .catch((error) => {
    console.error("Error:", error);
  });
```

<TabItem label="Go">

```go
package main

import (
    "bytes"
    "encoding/json"
    "fmt"
    "log"
    "net/http"
)

type Task struct {
    ClientKey   string      `json:"clientKey"`
    TaskDetails TaskDetails `json:"task"`
    LanguagePool string     `json:"languagePool"`
}

type TaskDetails struct {
    Type       string   `json:"type"`
    Module     string   `json:"module"`
    images     string[]  `json:"images"`
    WebsiteURL string   `json:"websiteURL"`
    Phrase     bool     `json:"phrase"`
    Case       bool     `json:"case"`
    Numeric    int      `json:"numeric"`
    Math       bool     `json:"math"`
    MinLength  int      `json:"minLength"`
    MaxLength  int      `json:"maxLength"`
    Score      float64  `json:"score"`
    Comment    string   `json:"comment"`
}

func main() {
    url := "https://api.nocaptchaai.com/createTask"

    taskData := Task{
        ClientKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
        TaskDetails: TaskDetails{
            Type:       "ImageToTextTask",
            Module:     "common",
            images:     [""], // string(single) or array(multiple) of base64 of the main images // string(single) or array(multiple) of base64 of the main images,
            WebsiteURL: "website URL",
            Phrase:     false,
            Case:       true,
            Numeric:    0,
            Math:       false,
            MinLength:  1,
            MaxLength:  5,
            Score:      0.8,
            Comment:    "enter the text you see on the image",
        },
        LanguagePool: "en",
    }

    jsonData, err := json.Marshal(taskData)
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatalf("Error marshalling JSON: %v", err)
    }

    req, err := http.NewRequest("POST", url, bytes.NewBuffer(jsonData))
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatalf("Error creating request: %v", err)
    }
    req.Header.Set("Content-Type", "application/json")

    client := &http.Client{}
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatalf("Error sending request: %v", err)
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    var responseBody []byte
    resp.Body.Read(responseBody)
    fmt.Println(string(responseBody))
}
```
